The question asks you to write Snort rules for each scenario.

1. Detect multiple failed FTP login attempts (possible brute force) on port 21

alert tcp any any -> any 21 (
    msg:"FTP Brute Force - Multiple Failed Logins";
    flow:to_client,established;
    content:"530 Login incorrect";
    detection_filter:track by_src, count 5, seconds 60;
    sid:1000001;
    rev:1;
)


---

2. Detect Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attempts containing <script> in HTTP requests

alert tcp any any -> any 80 (
    msg:"XSS Attempt - <script> detected";
    flow:to_server,established;
    content:"<script>";
    http_uri;
    nocase;
    sid:1000002;
    rev:1;
)


---

3. Detect DNS queries for domains ending with .top

alert udp any any -> any 53 (
    msg:"DNS Query for .top Domain";
    content:".top";
    nocase;
    sid:1000003;
    rev:1;
)


---

4. Detect communication with known malicious IP 198.51.100.25

alert ip any any <> 198.51.100.25 any (
    msg:"Communication with Known Malicious IP";
    sid:1000004;
    rev:1;
)


---

5. Detect TCP FIN scans targeting web server 192.168.10.50

alert tcp any any -> 192.168.10.50 80 (
    msg:"TCP FIN Scan Detected";
    flags:F;
    sid:1000005;
    rev:1;
)

These rules are suitable as standard Snort answers for a 10-mark exam.
